article.headline: Peters, Valparaiso top Texas Southern 84-73 in NIT

images.name: Valparaiso beats the Texas Southern press for the dunk.
images.caption: 2H (1:35) VALP Shane Hammink made Dunk. Assisted by Darien Walker.

article.linkText: Peters, Valparaiso top Texas Southern 84-73 in NIT
article.story:
VALPARAISO, Ind. -- Alec Peters scored 28 points and Valparaiso, one of four No. 1 seeds in the NIT, defeated Texas Southern 84-73 in an opening-round game on Tuesday night.

Keith Carter added 17 points and Darien Walker had 14 for the Crusaders (27-6), who got their first NIT win in their third appearance. Vashil Fernandez matched his career high with eight blocks.

Peters had 17 points in the first half when Valparaiso made 6 of 9 3-pointers and shot 50 percent for a 41-35 lead.

Texas Southern stayed with the Crusaders as the second half opened, making 8 of 12 shots. Then the Tigers went 1 of 10 from the field and fell behind by 11.

The lead reached double figures when Malcolm Riley received a technical for arguing a non-call on his missed 3-pointer. Peters made both free throws and on the ensuing possession, Darien Walker cut backdoor to throw down Shane Hammink's lob for a 66-55 lead with 9:56 to play.

Chris Thomas had 27 points, eight rebounds and seven assists for the Tigers (18-15). Derrick Griffin scored 18 on 7-of-9 shooting and Riley had 12 points with 11 rebounds.

videos.description: In the first half, Valparaiso's Shane Hammink puts up a nice lob to Darien Walker who finishes with the two-handed slam but then just seconds later Texas Southern answers with a dunk of their own, Derrick Griffin passes it up to Chris Thomas for the jam.
